- Kumari aka Living Goddess Nepal 
Nepal is relatively recent, dating only from the 17th century, the tradition of Kumari-Puja, or virgin worship, has been around for much longer. There is evidence of virgin worship taking place in Nepal for more than 2,300 years. It appears to have taken hold in Nepal in the 6th century. There is written evidence describing the selection, ornamentation and worship of the Kumari dating from the 13th century CE.

Instinctively choosing love over fear

Letting go of mistakes and failures

Opens the self to a whole new dimension of life
